<item>
            <title>[SPR-2168] @target() advices beans it should not</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-2168</link>
                <project id="10000" key="SPR">Spring Framework</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I have an aspect with a pointcut:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;@Around(&quot;@target(org.lds.stack.spring.serviceproxy.ServiceProxy)&quot;)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m using &amp;lt;aop:aspectj-autoproxy/&amp;gt; and a bean with the target class org.springframework.orm.jpa.JpaTemplate is getting proxied.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If I remove the pointcut then my JpaTemplate not longer gets proxied.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Mike&lt;/p&gt;</description>
